  				<h2 class="noTopMargin">C#/.NET Team Lead</h2>
	        	<p>Location: Cambridge, MA</p>
	        	<p>
	        	    We are looking for a .NET professional with 4-7 years of experience designing, developing, and managing Microsoft .NET projects.
	        	</p>    
            <h4>Job Responsibilities</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Work in Boston-area company offices or at Boston-area client sites alongside client IT staff</li>
                <li>Coordinate work and facilitate communication between client and offshore team</li>
                <li>Attend work prioritization and issue resolution meetings with our clients</li>
                <li>Ensure the team is consistently delivering working software</li>
                <li>Ensure the team is always working on the highest priority work and is aware of the priority</li>
                <li>Help ensure the progress of work the team is undertaking is clearly visible both to the team and to our clients</li>
                <li>Become well-versed in ScandiLabs' Knowledge Base and internal libraries, and contribute to their improvement</li>
                <li>Actively share knowledge with team members and across the company</li>
            </ul>
	        	    
            <h4>Qualifications</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>4+ years experience and expert knowledge of object-oriented software production in languages such as Java, Ruby, C++ or C#</li>
                <li>2+ years hands-on development experience with C#</li>
                <li>Hands-on experience with Visual Studio and intimate knowledge of MVC models</li>
                <li>Experience supporting and maintaining web applications</li>
                <li>Strong working knowledge of common web-based technologies such as HTML, JavaScript, CSS and AJAX</li>
                <li>Excellent oral and written communication skills</li>
                <li>Batch/command line, drools.NET and silverlight are big pluses</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h4>Education</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Bachelor's degree required, preferably with a computer science focus</li>
              <li>Additional course work and certificate programs preferred</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h4>Additional Requirements</h4>
            <p>Ability to work independently and as part of a team.  Service-oriented mindset.</p>
